Molecular chaperone: any protein that interacts with and aids in the folding or assembly of another protein without being part of its ﬁnal structure
Proteostasis: the state of balanced proteome found in healthy cells
Amyloid: disease-associated, ﬁbrillar aggregates with cross-β structure

