Stress proteins: cellular proteins whose expression is induced or increased under conditions of conformational stress; not all molecular chaperones are stress proteins
Aggregate: the association of two or more protein molecules in a nonfunctional state
Chaperonin: a class of structurally related molecular chaperones forming large, double-ring complexes that transiently enclose substrate protein for folding
TF: trigger factor
NAC: nascent-chainassociated complex
Nascent polypeptide: the polypeptide chain emerging from the ribosome during translation
